PClientConfig, ...)\n- Each scrape job's HTTPClientConfig validates and applies TLS settings\n\n### 5. Tracing Exporter TLS (tracing/tracing.go)\n\nOTLP tracing exporters enforce TLS distinctly for both protocols:\n\n**gRPC Tracers** (lines 182-194):\n- When insecure=false, creates TLS config via config_util.NewTLSConfig(&tracingCfg.TLSConfig)\n- Passes credentials via otlptracegrpc.WithTLSCredentials(credentials.NewTLS(tlsConf))\n\n**HTTP Tracers** (lines 206-228):\n- Always creates TLS config via config_util.NewTLSConfig(&tracingCfg.TLSConfig)\n- Passes config via otlptracehttp.WithTLSClientConfig(tlsConf)\n- Configuration change detection (line 76) forces manager restart to pick up new certificates\n\n### 6. Alertmanager Communications (notifier/alertmanagerset.go)\n\nAlertmanager clients created through:\n- NewAlertmanagerSet() uses AlertmanagerConfig with HTTPClientConfig\n- notifier/alertmanagerset.go (line 51): config_util.NewClientFromConfig(cfg.HTTPClientConfig, \"alertmanager\")\n\n### 7. Service Discovery Plugins (discovery/*/)\n\nMultiple service discovery mechanisms support TLS:\n\n**Triton SD** (discovery/triton/triton.go):\n- SDConfig has explicit TLSConfig field (line 68)\n- New() function creates TLS config via config.NewTLSConfig(&conf.TLSConfig) (line 154)\n\n**OpenStack SD** (discovery/openstack/openstack.go):\n- SDConfig has TLSConfig field (line 65)\n- NewDiscoverer() applies TLS config (line 197)\n\n**xDS/Kuma SD** (discovery/xds/):\n- SDConfig in xds.go (line 52) has HTTPClientConfig\n- KumaSDConfig in kuma.go uses HTTPClientConfig with TLS\n- xds/client.go creates HTTP clients with TLS validation\n\n**HTTP SD** (discovery/http/http.go):\n- SDConfig with HTTPClientConfig for TLS\n\n**Other Cloud Providers** (discovery/{consul,aws/*,azure,nomad,puppetdb,uyuni}/*):\n- All cloud discovery integrations (EC2, ECS, ElastiCache, MSK, Consul, Azure, Nomad, PuppetDB, Uyuni, etc.) use HTTPClientConfig with NewClientFromConfig() for TLS\n\n## TLS Validation Pathway\n\nAll TLS configuration flows through github.com/prometheus/common/config.HTTPClientConfig which provides:\n1. **Validation**: HTTPClientConfig.Validate() checks certificate paths and permission\n2. **Client Creation**: NewClientFromConfig() applies certificates to http.Client\n3. **Certificate Loading**: SetDirectory() resolves relative paths to absolute paths\n\n## Certificate Handling\n\nTLS certificates are handled through:\n- CA certificates (CAFile, CAData)\n- Client certificates (CertFile, CertData) \n- Client key (KeyFile, KeyData)\n- InsecureSkipVerify flag\n- ServerName for SNI validation\n\nAll configuration types implement SetDirectory() methods to resolve relative certificate paths, ensuring certificates are properly located at runtime.\n\n## Enforcement Points\n\n1. **Configuration Loading**: config.Load() in config/config.go (line 74)\n2. **Configuration Validation**: Each config type's UnmarshalYAML() and Validate() methods\n3. **Client Creation**: All external connections use NewClientFromConfig() which applies TLS settings\n4. **Web Server**: toolkit_web.Validate() and ServeMultiple() enforce web TLS\n5. **Tracing**: buildTracerProvider() and getClient() enforce tracer TLS with certificate reloading\n\nThe architecture ensures TLS is applied consistently across all external interfaces through the HTTPClientConfig abstraction, with explicit TLS config structures for tracing and service discovery plugins."
